  "body": "I'm trying to verify the nonce that produced through ethash in contract, so that I can verify the memory of a computer. but the problem is that the ethash algorithm must have a cache of 16M at least to verify,  \r\nwhile it is inefficient through contract to implement it, so I'm try to add a new opcode or modify an existing opcode like opdifficulty to complete the same function, but the problem is that when I compile the new contract which my new opcode in, it throw erros `Error: Different number of arguments in return statement than in returns declaration. return block.difficulty(....)`\r\nso what can i do to add a new opcode or modify an existing opcode which new parameter or return type?\r\n\r\nOr is there any other method that can verify the ethash's nonce?\r\nOr is there any other method that can verify a computer's memory?",
